Competencies

CSS prescribes the rules by which elements appear on the view of a page
Without CSS your pages would look very dull
Can be injected directly into the HTML, or linked from another document
Normally, CSS is referenced from another document as a shortcut instead of manually styling each element
Not expected to know all CSS rules and syntax, expected to know you can reference the docs
CSS packages and frameworks exists for you to have preloaded styles (Bootstrap)



Applications
Understand when and why to inject CSS directly or link from external document
Style your HTML page
Incorporate linked stylesheets 
Understand grid and box layouts

W3Schools CSS tutorial:

https://www.w3schools.com/css/

Different ways to link your styles:

http://matthewjamestaylor.com/blog/adding-css-to-html-with-link-embed-inline-and-import
